---

## ✅ Topics Completed So Far

### 1️⃣ Introduction to Computer Networks
Computer networking ki basics — network kya hota hai, evolution of computer networks, uses aur types of networks (LAN, MAN, WAN).

### 2️⃣ OSI Model & TCP/IP Model
7-layer OSI model aur 4-layer TCP/IP model ka detailed comparison — har layer ka role, protocols aur real-world mapping.

### 3️⃣ Network Topologies
Bus, Star, Ring, Mesh, Tree aur Hybrid topology — structure, advantages/disadvantages ke saath diagrams.

### 4️⃣ IP Addressing (IPv4 & IPv6)
IPv4 (32-bit) vs IPv6 (128-bit), Network ID/Host ID, Address Classes (A–E), loopback & broadcast address, real-world examples — diagrams ke saath.

---

## 🔜 Coming Up Next

- **Classful Addressing (Class A–E)** — deep dive into class ranges & binary derivation
- **Subnetting & CIDR** — subnet mask calculation, CIDR notation, VLSM
- **Network ID, Host ID & Broadcast Address** — practical numericals
- **Topology + VPN** — how VPNs work over different topologies
- **Dark Web and Internetworking** — internetworking devices, dark web basics
- **Transport Layer (TCP/UDP)** — connection-oriented vs connectionless, flow/error control
- **Routing & Switching Basics** — static/dynamic routing, switching techniques
- **DNS, DHCP & Application Layer Protocols** — how domain resolution & dynamic IP allocation work

---

## 🛠️ How I'm Building These Notes

- Lecture notes ko organize karke point-wise explanation
- Har topic me relevant **diagrams** included
- Real-world examples jaha applicable ho
- Notes `.md` ya `.pdf` format me maintained

